## Three levels of cognitive loading

| Level | When loaded | Token cost | Content |
|---|---|---|---|
| Metadata | Always, at startup | ~100 tokens | YAML frontmatter — agent knows skill exists |
| Instructions | When skill triggers | <5k tokens | SKILL.md body — reasoning, thresholds, tool calls |
| Resources | Only when referenced | Unlimited | references/, scripts/, assets/ |

## Shared infrastructure (unchanged by migration)

These stay flat in `application/` — they are NOT capability slices:
- `core/` — pure models, protocols, rules
- `stores/` — persistence implementations
- `tools/` — agent tool providers
- `events/` — event feed delivery

## Runtime skills today

Currently, runtime skills for the director agent live in `.remi/skills/` and are
discovered via `skills_paths:` in the director manifest. After migration, skills
will live in `application/<capability>/SKILL.md` and ship with the package.

## Migration rules

- Migrate one capability at a time — never big-bang.
- Each migrated capability must pass existing tests before merge.
- Agent manifests move from `agents/<name>/app.yaml` to `<capability>/scripts/app.yaml`.
- Update `capabilities.py` shell wiring to point to new locations.
